{{outlet}}
<div id="welcome-page" class="page">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero center">
      <h1>
        Visualisation tool for public spending data has arrived
      </h1>
      <p class="flow-text">
        Raw and dirty public spending data visualised into a sexy, tidy, filterable node network. Thatâ€™s Elvis. We are still in beta, so feedback is welcome!
      </p>
      <br>
      <div>
          <a href="#" class="btn-large transparent hide">Use ready-made network</a>
            {{#link-to 'network.new' class="btn-large primary"}}Create a network{{/link-to}}
          {{#if session.isAuthenticated}}
          {{else}}
            {{#link-to 'account.new' class="btn-large primary"}}Create an account{{/link-to}}
          {{/if}}
      </div>
      <br>
      <br>
      <div class="node-types">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s4 center-align">
            <div class="figure-buyer"></div>
            <h4>
              Governments
            </h4>
            <p class="small">
              Examine preferences of government institutions such as municipalities, ministries and others
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col s4 center-align">
            <div class="figure-bidder"></div>
            <h4>Companies</h4>
            <p class="small">
              Discover which companies sell their goods and services to the governments
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col s4 center-align">
            <div class="figure-relationship"></div>
            <h4>Contracts</h4>
            <p class="small">
              Dig into public contract details and money flows
            </p>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="full-width section-about">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12">
            <h1 class="big-title">
              A tool for revealing corruption
            </h1>
            <p class="flow-text big-content">
              'Tendering' is a process where governments hire private companies that provide services for our tax money. Dive with us into 7 million public tenders in Europe.
            </p>
            <p>
              Elvis helps you create public spending network in specific EU country, time and sector. Explore relationships between government and companies. You can ask questions like "Who is dominatig IT market in Netherlands?" or "Which companies earn most money from public spending in Slovakia?"
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col m6">
            <h3 class="title">
              Under development
            </h3>
            <p class="content">
              Feedback = {{fa-icon 'heart'}}
              Have an opinion? Everybody does. If you'd like to share yours, you can reach us on the links below.
            </p>
            <div class="links">
              <div class="link">
                <!--incont-->
                {{fa-icon 'smile-o'}}<a href="https://talk.tenders.exposed">Join the Elvis community</a>
              </div>
              <div class="link">
                {{fa-icon 'envelope-o'}}<a href="mailto:tech@tenders.exposed">Contact us</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col m6">
            <h3 class="title">
              Free and Open-source
            </h3>
            <p class="content">
              We are open source!
              Would you like to help us with development or even make your own Elvis? Our Elvis is yor Elvis
            </p>
            <div class="links">
              <div class="link">
                <!--incont-->
                {{fa-icon 'github'}}<a href="https://github.com/tenders-exposed">Elvis on GitHub</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col m6">
            <h3 class="title">
              Data source
            </h3>
            <p class="content">
              Data
              We are using local and EU tender data from the <a href="https://digiwhist.eu">Digiwhist project</a>. Maps, graphs, dashboards, data download and more tender fun is available on <a href="opentender.eu">opentender.eu</a>
            </p>
            <div class="links">
              <div class="link">
                <!--incont-->
                {{! {{fa-icon 'arrow-right'}\}<a href="#">About TED data</a> }}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col m6">
            <h3 class="title">
              Based on research
            </h3>
            <p class="content">
              It's no mumbo-jumbo. There is an interesting research behind this idea. Learn about Red Flags and how we evaluate the data.
            </p>
            <div class="links">
              <div class="link">
                <!--incont-->
                {{fa-icon 'arrow-right'}}<a href="http://v3.sk/~naberacka/social_network_analysis_public_procurement_data_journalism.pdf">Read the thesis</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
